caption: Food was great!! I'm comparing it from what they serve out in twin falls!!! Very little contact with employees since you order and pay of an iPad of sorts but non the less the little interaction we had with eMployees was good and friendly. Was worth our two hour drive out of twin for some decent grub.

This place is hard to find on google maps but worth the 6 times I drove in circles. I had the Apocalypse roll and their Charmander & Moneybags combo. All of it was delicious and the ambience was very modern simplistic. Will be returning.
There is nothing quite like fresh fried rice and it did not disappoint. The food was delicious and I would eat here again.

The food is delicious, but very disappointed with recent changes. After moving two blocks down they no longer offer free water cups, so I purchased an arizona tea just to realize they don't actually sell that. Not sure why it was listed on the menu. Also very sad that they removed banana boats from the menu, pretty sure they don't offer any desserts under the "sides and desserts" tab.
Probably the best sushi in boise, very affordable and a fantastic selection!  Restaurant is immaculate!

Dharma is a sit-down restaurant that provides a menu of mainly sushi with some Thai food and even "loaded tots". You order food online or through easy-to-use kiosks that allows you to quickly order without having to wait for a waitress. The food is a tasty fusion of flavor and made to order with friendly staff that brings the food to your table. It's great for a quick bite or takeout.

I work in downtown Boise and love picking up food from Dharma! The restaurant is always clean and the staff friendly and helpful. The recent negative reviews are only because they are enforcing the city and county-wide mask mandates so that they can stay in business. Some people are a little salty about that.
Terrible service,  or none at all!  Food ok. Never had anyone check on during entire meal,, did not serve napkins..  not impressed!

so to start, the sushi here is god awful. imagine the subway of sushi, that’s dharma. anyone that likes GOOD and authentic sushi should go literally anywhere else. they don’t even hand roll the sushi! on top of that, my boyfriend works here, pretty soon will not be. this is because the owners have no respect for their staff and the staff are horribly under appreciated. the higher up staff here needs to learn how to take their employees seriously when they have issues, and learn how to take care of a restaurant. like i said terrible sushi and terrible owners. i will never be returning.
My girlfriend and I love Dharma! They are always super friendly, the atmosphere can’t be beat, self service is convenient, and the sushi tastes amazing!

Delicious sushi; my favorite is the Lebowski roll, my husband loves the rice bowls. The new location is great because it has free parking and so many wonderful plants inside. Folks who work there are super nice.

the new location is terrible. changed everything about Dharma that boise locals loved. the new menu is pathetic, not at all vegan inclusive anymore seeing how they replaced tofu with... seasoned beets??? also?? who cuts green onions vertically? why do you do that now it’s weird. i just ate one piece of the roll i ordered 5 minutes ago, asked for no beets, got beets, and the rice was literally cooked into a mushy paste.. i’d put 0 stars if i could. Dharma, please reverse the awful changes y’all made..
Constantly cancel my DoorDash orders, never answer the phones and everything has different hours.
The lack of HUMAN interaction really displeased me. I truly hope this isn’t the way restaurants are going. If I wanted to order on a screen I would have ordered online

My husband and I have gone to Dharma for a couple years now and it’s our favorite place to get sushi. Last night when we ordered I was bummed to see that they got rid of the save the fish roll that I always get. I was able to modify a new roll to the old one but still it was more expensive than the save the fish roll. Today when I went to eat my leftovers for lunch I bit into the roll and there was plastic wrap in it which was definitely off-putting.

Tobra (sorry if I misspell) & her co-workers were so amazing tonight! They exceeded my customer service expectations and went over the top to make my night! My fiance & sister love Dharma and they will not disappoint.🙌🏻☺️ Plus the new place has an awesome vibe!✌🏻💕

Our new favorite sushi place in Boise.  Fresh ingredients, great flavors and fast service.  This is the first place I’ve been in where you order on computers in the establishment, I dig it.  Tater tots are also phenomenal, highly recommend.
They have good sushi but can't roll em to save their lives.  . . Bring a spoon.
Great sushi. Cold drinks. Friendly atmosphere

Nice place would recommend

My girlfriend and I go here about 2 times a week for almost 3 years and love the food! BUT served my vegetarian girlfriend shrimp and caused her to be extremely sick.

Every time I order from them they have a very safe environment for pick up, no dining-in which minimizes risk, staff are always wearing masks, and just generally their food travels very well with to-go orders.

The girl and guy that closed tonight we’re the nicest people we have encountered at dharma and are definitely the reason we would come back again. Thank you so much for helping us tonight you are truly wonderful people!

Dharma is so tasty, it has outlasted any relationship I've had - let me explain. After visiting Dharma for the first time with someone I was seeing and deciding it was our go-to stop for great sushi at great prices, we visited multiple times after that first visit and established my love for sushi. While the relationship may be over, that amazing customer service experience tied with their tasty sushi is far from over. I will continue to visit Dharma and look forward to some future dates and great meals here! Cheers!

They gave half our order to the next table, then told us they couldn't make another of one of the dishes. We asked to refund that dish, the person ignored that request and started suggesting substitute dishes. We accepted a substitute, waited another 30 minutes for them to remake half the order, then they forgot a dish. More waiting. The sushi was good but the management and service are awful.

ABSOLUTELY worst experience of my families life in a Boise Idaho "restaraunt". Bad customer service both times I've eaten there and that has been enough for me. I'll never bother eating there again. In desperate need of new management and employees working the register as well as putting the food together. 40 minute wait time for sushi and there was still no urgency or hustle. Don't bother wasting your time or money.

It was nice using the online order process. It made it simple to place the order and pick it up. Although, the app did say my order would be ready in 15-20 minutes it did take about 10 minutes longer. Which was understandable with how busy they were. I was grateful I ordered online because if I would have walked in it may have taken longer. Other than that the food was delicious and would recommend Dharma's to any sushi lovers!
Great place

While I am not a local and have never eaten at Dharma's, their commitment to public safety has prompted me to throw them a 5-Star rating.  Small businesses are the backbone of America. Those "essential" employees are what keep this country running. It is with their hard earned sweat, perseverance, and putting their own health at risk to give you a place to stuff your ignorant opinions while stuffing your faces.  If you have never eaten there, do you really have any right to leave a negative comment? Of coarse you do - this IS America. But, that same privilege afforded to you is the same right Dharma has to refuse to serve whom ever they please, for whatever reason they deem fit. Those rights came at a cost - something your entitled/whiny selves wouldn't know anything about.  If you want to whine and complain about somewhere you have never been, regarding food you have never eaten - pay a shrink.  On another note - kuddos to the owner for standing up for your employees and establishment. And I LOVE the comments you leave!!

This place is by no means a world class sushi joint. But they're fast, efficient, and inexpensive. And it's always clean and the staff are always helpful. For a fast food sushi place, they do what they do very well. If you're in the mood for some decent food at a great price and need it fast, check this place out. 😉
Some of the best sushi I've ever had. Very respectful

A unique place in Boise, recommended for fast sushi lunch downtown. Surprisingly fresh fish, although the raw options are pretty narrow (Salmon or Tuna.)  The cucumber salad is simple and tasty, and I recommend "Name the Fish", Always Sunny, and Nirvana rolls, which are big enough to share with a side.
Great service
Good beer and vegan options. Very much appreciate their commitment to public health and safety. All Dharma employees deserve a raise

Fabulous food, amazing service, over all a 100/10. It’s greatly appreciated the owners are so strict and concerned for customer and employee wellbeing. There’s always gonna be a few Karen’s trying to act out of selfishness.
Great food and great service! I tried the fried tofu and crab puffs. Both were cooked perfectly and very flavorful. Will definitely go back. Thank you!
